This paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms and their potential for discrimination, which falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). It also discusses the legal and ethical implications of such discrimination, which could fall under "Computers and Society" (cs.CY) and "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). The paper also proposes strategies for detecting and preventing discrimination in machine learning algorithms, which falls under "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Emerging Technologies" (cs.ET).
